			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="text-decoration: underline">MULTIPLE MAGICIAN GROUPS</span>
<br />

<br />
This piece focuses on having at least one more magician to partner with.
<br />

<br />
1. You will still be benefitted by pulling with a low aggro spell.
<br />

<br />
2. Unlike the soloing circumstance, the earth pet is more optional than a requirement. The Air pet works well in this scenario.
<br />

<br />
3. Casting a Malaise-type spell on the mob is also optional, but still useful.
<br />

<br />
4. You will still need to do at least some direct damage to the mob in order to keep the pets from taking 75% of the experience. Aggro is less of a concern with two pets on a mob, so heavier nuking is less risky than solo.
<br />

<br />
5. The key to successful chaining groups is making sure to time the pet recast such that there is always at least one pet on the mob. This may mean staggering your recasts so neither magician is reclaiming at the same time, and neither pet is near death at the same time either. This will take some practice. Also, it will probably mean that pets will have to be reclaimed prematurely (before they drop too low in hit points.) Mana use is minimal, so extra mana use from premature reclaiming shouldn't be a concern.
<br />

<br />
6. Once the mob is dead, loot at will. You will be able to pull again immediately. Just like in the solo circumstance, meditation between fights is completely unnecessary.</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Jochan Galadar on Wed Dec 24, 2003 7:58 pm; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
