				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The key to successful chaining groups is making sure to time the pet recast such that there is always at least one pet on the mob. This may mean staggering your recasts so neither magician is reclaiming at the same time</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />

<br />
This is fairly simple to overcome.
<br />

<br />
Have one mage send his pet in as if he was solo. Once the pet is close to "critical reclaim" hp's have the second mage send his in and reclaim/recast the first. Rinse and repeat.
<br />

<br />
This way is just a safer way of doing it solo style. You will always have a pet on the mob and won't have to worry about any mistakes or early root breaks.
<br />

<br />
Another advantage to this is you will have 2 mages to "burn it down" once the mob gets low on hitpoints. 
<br />

<br />
Also works well with mobs that enrage. One pet will have the aggro and be /back off'd the other ( with taunt turned off) can deal the damage from behind.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234133" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ghetto_and_Proud</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
